These are a quick snapshot of what you need to become a registered contractor with the National Construction Authority (NCA) in Kenya The following are the six must have requirements when registering with the NCA Foreign contractors willing to register with National Construction Authority to operate in Kenya are required to pay a registration fee of Ksh. 100, 000 and must undertake only tenders they win. Those registering under a temporary registration will need to commit to sub-contracting “not less that 30% of the value” of contract to local contractors   